{"title_page": "List of Washburn Ichabods head football coaches", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=October 2013}}\n[[File:Bennie Owen.jpg|thumb|right|Bennie Owen coached at Washburn for the 1900 season before going to the [[Bethany Terrible Swedes]] and later the [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma Sooners]].  He ended his career with a record of 155\u201360\u201319 and was inducted into the [[College Football Hall of Fame]] in 1951.]]\nThe [[Washburn Ichabods football]] program is a [[college football]] team that represents [[Washburn University]] in the [[Mid-America Intercollegiate Athletics Association]], a part of [[NCAA Division II]].  The team has had 38 head coaches since its first recorded football game in 1891.<ref>{{cite web\n |last=Shafer \n |first=Ian \n |title=Washburn University (All seasons results) \n |publisher=College Football Reference \n |url=http://cfreference.net/cfr/school/washburn/328/all-seasons \n |accessdate=March 16, 2013 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304051601/http://cfreference.net/cfr/school/washburn/328/all-seasons \n |archivedate=March 4, 2016 \n}}\n</ref> The current coach is [[Craig Schurig]] who first took the position for the 2002 season.<ref>{{Cite web\n|last=DeLassus\n|first=David\n|title=Washburn (KS) Records by Year (incomplete data)\n|publisher=[[College Football Data Warehouse]]\n|url=http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/incomplete_data/year_by_year_current.php?teamid=3420\n|accessdate=March 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wusports.com/documents/2007/7/30/07fbguide-127-137-history1.pdf?id=69|publisher=[[Washburn University]]|title=2007 Football Media Guide|accessdate=March 16, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Key==\n{{List of college football program head coaches key}}\n\n==Coaches==\nStatistics correct as of the end of the 2017 college football season.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!No.!!Name!!Term!!GC!!OW