 is [[Craig Schurig]] who first took the position for the 2002 season.<ref>{{Cite web\n|last=DeLassus\n|first=David\n|title=Washburn (KS) Records by Year (incomplete data)\n|publisher=[[College Football Data Warehouse]]\n|url=http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/incomplete_data/year_by_year_current.php?teamid=3420\n|accessdate=March 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wusports.com/documents/2007/7/30/07fbguide-127-137-history1.pdf?id=69|publisher=[[Washburn University]]|title=2007 Football Media Guide|accessdate=March 16, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Key==\n{{List of college football program head coaches key}}\n\n==Coaches==\nStatistics correct as of the end of the 2017 college football season.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n!No.!!Name!!Term!!GC!!OW!!OL!!OT!!O%!!CW!!CL!!CT!!C%!!PW!!PL!!CCs!!NCs!!class=\"unsortable\"|Awards\n|-\n|0|| Unknown ||{{sort|1891|1891&ndash;1893}}||10||2||8||0||{{Winning percentage|2|8|0}}||0||0||0||||0||0||0||0||{{ntsh|0}}\n|-\n|1|| [[W. M. Gains]] ||{{sort|1894|1894}}||5||3||2||0||{{Winning percentage|3|2|0}}||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\n|-\n|X|| ''no team'' ||{{sort|1894|1894}}||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014|{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||\n|-\n|2|| [[W. Griffith]] ||{{sort|1896|1896}}||9||7||1||1||{{Winning percentage|7|1|1}}||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\u2014||{{ntsh|0}}\n|-\n|3|| [[Paul Coldren]] ||{{sort|1897|1897&ndash;1898}}||19||15||3||1||{{Winning percentage|15|3|1}}||0||0||0||||0||0||0||0||{{ntsh|0}}\n|-\n|4|| [[William Melford]] ||{{sort|1899|1899}}||9||2||5||2||{{Winning percentage|2|5|2}}||{{ntsh|