{"title_page": "Contingent value rights", "text_new": "{{unreferenced|date=December 2017}}\nIn [[corporate finance]], \n'''Contingent Value Rights''' (CVR) are [[Contractual rights|rights]] granted by an [[Mergers and acquisitions |acquirer]] to a company\u2019s [[shareholders]], <ref>[[Investopedia]] (2020). [http://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/cvr.asp ''Contingent Value Right (CVR)'']</ref> facilitating the transaction where some uncertainty is inherent.\nCVRs may be separately tradeable [[Security (finance)| securities]]; they are occasionally acquired (or [[short (finance)|shorted]]) by specialized [[hedge fund]]s.\n\n==Forms==\nThese rights typically take either of two forms:<ref>[[Thomson Reuters]] (2019). [http://www.wlrk.com/webdocs/wlrknew/AttorneyPubs/WLRK.26465.19.pdf ''Contingent Value Rights (CVRs)''], Practical Law series</ref>\n(1) Event-driven CVRs compensate the owners for yet to eventuate positive developments in their business - hence also protecting the acquirer against [[valuation risk]].\n(2) Price-protection CVRs are granted when [[Mergers_and_acquisitions#Stock |payment is share based]], providing a [[hedge (finance)|hedge]] against downside [[price risk]] in the acquirer's equity. <ref name=\"Chatterjee\"/>\n\nIn the first case, CVRs are granted \n<ref>[[Motley Fool]] (2018). [https://www.fool.com/investing/2018/10/19/what-is-a-contingent-value-right.aspx ''What Is a Contingent Value Right?'']</ref> \nin scenarios in which the acquiring company does not wish to pay for a product that might not work, has a limited market, or might need significant investment;\nwhereas on the other side, the acquired company \u201cwants to get full value for its assets\u201d.\nThe CVR then \u201chelps bridge this negotiation\u201d.\nUnder these rights, shareholders will receive additional cash, securities, or benefits if a specific and named event occurs \n- one where the value of the firm significantly increases\n- within a specified timeframe. \nCVRs are very common in the [[:Category:Life sciences industry |biotech]] and [[Pharmaceutical industry |pharmaceutical industries]]; they are also often granted to shareholders in companies facing significant,  [[Accretion (finance) |value accretive]] restructuring. \nFor an example see [[Media General]] / [[Nexstar Media Group]].\n\nThe second case, protection against price risk, is facilitated by specifying that payment will be made at an averaged, as opposed to final, share price; a floor may also be set. <ref>[[U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission|SEC]] (2006). [https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1094961/000119312506126810/dex991.htm ''Questions and Answers For Contingent Value Rights Holders'']</ref>\n\n==Valuation==\nUnder both, the CVR is in function, a form of [[Option (finance)|option]].\n<ref>Jan W Dash (2004). [https://books.google.co.za/books/about/Quantitative_Finance_and_Risk_Management.html?id=wGVIDQAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y ''Quantitative Finance and Risk Management: A Physicist's Approach''], World Scientific. {{ISBN|978-9812387127}}</ref>\n\nThe first case: analogous to a [[call option]], the payout to the CVR holder will be triggered by the event occurring, and will be zero otherwise.\nTo [[valuation (finance)|determine the value]] of these rights, \nanalysts will apply a modified [[option pricing]] model based on the probability of the event, the time horizon specified, and the corresponding payout rules; \nsee [[contingent claim valuation]]\n<ref>[[Aswath Damodaran]] (ND). [http://pages.stern.nyu.edu/~adamodar/New_Home_Page/lectures/approach.html ''Valuation: Approaches & Discounted Cash Flow Models'']</ref>.\n\nThe second: the CVR takes the form of a modified [[Asian option]].<ref name=\"Chatterjee\">Sris Chatterjee (2003). [http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=424903 ''Contingent Value Rights in Acquisitions: Theory and Empirical Evidence''], EFA 2003 Annual Conference Paper No. 897</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/cvr.asp CVR on Investopedia]\n*[https://www.fool.com/investing/2018/10/19/what-is-a-contingent-value-right.aspx CVR on Motley Fool]\n*[https://www.forbes.com/sites/greatspeculations/2011/05/09/shadowy-shares-the-dark-side-of-contingent-value-rights/#425e23603343 Shadowy Shares: The Dark Side of Contingent Value Rights, Forbes.com]  (Michael Stocker, Iona Evan. 2011)\n\n[[Category:Corporate finance]]\n[[Category:Mergers and acquisitions]]\n[[Category:Valuation (finance)]]\n[[Category:Securities (finance)]]\n[[Category:Real options]]\n[[Category:Equity securities]]\n", "text_old": "{{unreferenced|date=December 2017}}\nIn [[corporate finance]], \n'''Contingent Value Rights''' (CVR) are [[Contractual rights|rights]] granted by an [[Mergers and acquisitions |acquirer]] to a company\u2019s [[shareholders]], <ref>[[Investopedia]] (2020). [http://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/cvr.asp ''Contingent Value Right (CVR)'']</ref> facilitating the transaction where some uncertainty is inherent.\nCVRs may be separately tradeable [[Security (finance)| securities]]; they are occasionally acquired (or [[short (finance)|shorted]]) by specialized [[hedge fund]]s.\n\n==Forms==\nThese rights typically take either of two forms:<ref>[[Thomson Reuters]] (2019). [http://www.wlrk.com/webdocs/wlrknew/AttorneyPubs/WLRK.26465.19.pdf ''Contingent Value Rights (CVRs)''], Practical Law series</ref>\n(1) Event-driven CVRs compensate the owners for yet to eventuate positive developments in their business - hence also protecting the acquirer against [[valuation risk]].\n(2) Price-protection CVRs are granted when [[Mergers_and_acquisitions#Stock |payment is share based]], providing a [[hedge (finance)|hedge]] against downside [[price risk]] in the acquirer's equity. <ref name=\"Chatterjee\"/>\n\nIn the first case, CVRs are granted \n<ref>[[Motley Fool]] (2018). [https://www.fool.com/investing/2018/10/19/what-is-a-contingent-value-right.aspx ''What Is a Contingent Value Right?'']</ref> \nin scenarios in which the acquiring company does not wish to pay for a product that might not work, has a limited market, or might need significant investment;\nwhereas on the other side, the acquired company \u201cwants to get full value for its assets\u201d.\nThe CVR then \u201chelps bridge this negotiation\u201d.\nUnder these rights, shareholders will receive additional cash, securities, or benefits if a specific and named event occurs \n- one where the value of the firm significantly increases\n- within a specified timeframe. \nCVRs are very common in the [[:Category:Life sciences industry |biotech]] and [[Pharmaceutical industry |pharmaceutical industries]]; they are also often granted to shareholders in companies facing significant,  [[Accretion (finance) |value accretive]] restructuring. \nFor an example see [[Media General]] / [[Nexstar Media Group]].\n\nThe second case, protection against price risk, is facilitated by specifying that payment will be made at an averaged, as opposed to final, share price; a floor may also be set. <ref>[[U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission|SEC]] (2006). [https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1094961/000119312506126810/dex991.htm ''Questions and Answers For Contingent Value Rights Holders'']</ref>\n\n==Valuation==\nUnder both, the CVR is in function, a form of [[Option (finance)|option]].\n<ref>Jan W Dash (2004). [https://books.google.co.za/books/about/Quantitative_Finance_and_Risk_Management.html?id=wGVIDQAAQBAJ&redir_esc=y ''Quantitative Finance and Risk Management: A Physicist's Approach''], World Scientific. {{ISBN|978-9812387127}}</ref>\n\nThe first case: analogous to a [[call option]], the payout to the CVR holder will be triggered by the event occurring, and will be zero otherwise.\nTo [[valuation (finance)|determine the value]] of these rights, \nanalysts will apply a modified [[option pricing]] model based on the probability of the event, the time horizon specified, and the corresponding payout rules; \nsee [[contingent claim valuation]]\n<ref>[[Aswath Damodaran]] (ND). [http://pages.stern.nyu.edu/~adamodar/New_Home_Page/lectures/approach.html ''Valuation: Approaches & Discounted Cash Flow Models'']</ref>.\n\nThe second: the CVR takes the form of a modified [[Asian option]].<ref name=\"Chatterjee\">Sris Chatterjee (2003). [http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=424903 ''Contingent Value Rights in Acquisitions: Theory and Empirical Evidence''], EFA 2003 Annual Conference Paper No. 897</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.investopedia.com/terms/c/cvr.asp CVR on Investopedia]\n*[https://www.fool.com/investing/2018/10/19/what-is-a-contingent-value-right.aspx CVR on Motley Fool]\n*[http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=424903 Contingent Value Rights in Acquisitions: Theory and Empirical Evidence]\n*[https://www.forbes.com/sites/greatspeculations/2011/05/09/shadowy-shares-the-dark-side-of-contingent-value-rights/#425e23603343 Shadowy Shares: The Dark Side of Contingent Value Rights, Forbes.com]  (Michael Stocker, Iona Evan. 2011)\n\n[[Category:Corporate finance]]\n[[Category:Mergers and acquisitions]]\n[[Category:Valuation (finance)]]\n[[Category:Securities (finance)]]\n[[Category:Real options]]\n[[Category:Equity securities]]\n", "name_user": "Fintor", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Contingent_value_rights"}
{"title_page": "Kanpur Metro", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox Public transit\n| box_width        = \n| name             = Kanpur Metro\n| image            = Kanpur Metro Map.png\n| imagesize        = 300px\n| image2           = \n| imagesize2       = \n| native_name      =\n| locale           = [[Kanpur, India|Kanpur]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| transit_type     = [[Rapid transit]]\n| lines            = 2 (Approved & Under construction, Phase I & II)\n| stations         = 30 (Approved, Phase I & II, 22 stations in a 23.785 km stretch and 8 stations in 8.6 km stretch)\n| key_people       = \n| ridership        = \n| headquarters     =  Near Uttar Pradesh State Textile Corporation Limited, [[Grand Trunk Road]], Sharda Nagar, Kanpur\n| owner            = [[ Uttar Pradesh Metro Rail Corporation]]                                  | began_operation  = December 2021 or January 2022 {phase 1} i.e.(IIT-KANPUR to Motijheel)  \n| vehicles         = \n| train_length     = 3 coaches\n| headway          = 4 minutes\n| system_length    {{convert|34.78|km|mi|abbr=on}} \n| track_gauge      = {{Track gauge|sg|allk=on}}\n| el               = 25 [[Kilovolt|Kv]] [[Electric current|AC]] [[THIRD RAIL]]\n| top_speed        = 80 km/h\n| map              = \n}}\n'''Kanpur Metro''' is a rail-based mass transit system which is under construction for the city of [[Kanpur]], [[India]], and extendable to the [[Kanpur metropolitan area]].  The feasibility study for the project was done by [[RITES]] in June 2015\n. The study was prepared to control traffic woes and congestion, which are hampering the growth, development, and prosperity of the city area. The tenders were floated for the elevated viaduct between IIT to Motijheel. [[Shapoorji Pallonji Group|AFCONS Infra]] has been awarded the tender. Elevated viaduct work has begun.The barricading has been done in the middle of the road from IIT Kanpur till Rawatpur and more than 50 pillars are constructed till 5th March,2020. The pillars are being erected and construction work is going in full swing. Construction of station near IIT has also started (dated 5th,March 2020).\n\nOn 28 February 2019, the Central government approved the metro project for [[Kanpur]] at an estimated cost of \u20b911,076.48 crores and a five-year time limit.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/business/business-news/cabinet-approves-kanpur-metro-rail-project/articleshow/68208021.cms|title=\u0915\u0948\u092c\u093f\u0928\u0947\u091f \u0928\u0947 \u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u0930\u0947\u0932 \u092a\u0930\u093f\u092f\u094b\u091c\u0928\u093e \u0915\u094b \u092e\u0902\u091c\u0942\u0930\u0940 \u0926\u0947 \u0926\u0940|date=2019-02-28|website=Navbharat Times|language=hi|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/adityanath-thanks-modi-for-clearing-agra-kanpur-metro-projects/1488020|title=Adityanath thanks Modi for clearing Agra, Kanpur Metro projects|website=outlookindia.com/|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref> The [[European Investment Bank]] has proposed to provide a Euro 650 million loan for the project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themetrorailguy.com/2020/03/31/eib-evaluating-e650mn-loan-for-kanpur-metro-phase-1/|title=EIB Evaluating \u20ac650 mn Loan for Kanpur Metro Phase 1|date=2020-03-31|website=The Metro Rail Guy|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==Corridors==\n\n==={{font color|Red|Line I (Red Line)}} - 8 Underground, 14 Elevated===\n== Stations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"100%\" \n|-\n! style=\"background:#FFDF00;\" colspan=\"9\" | <span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Line-1'''</span>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''#'''</span>\n! colspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Station Name'''</span>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Phase'''</span>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Opening'''</span>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Station Layout'''</span><tr>\n<th><span style=\"color:Black;\">'''English'''</span></th>\n<th><span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Hindi'''</span></th></tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>'''IIT Kanpur Station'''\n</td>\n<td>'''\u0906\u0908\u0906\u0908\u091f\u0940 \u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0947\u0936\u0928'''</td><td>1\n</td><td>2024\n</td><td>Elevated\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>'''Kalyanpur Railway Station'''\n</td>\n<td>'''\u0915\u0932\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0923\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u0930\u0947\u0932\u0935\u0947 \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0947\u0936\u0928 '''</td><td>1\n</td><td>2024\n</td><td>Elevated\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>'''SPM Hospital Station'''\n</td>\n<td>'''\u090f\u0938\u092a\u0940\u090f\u092e \u0905\u0938\u094d\u092a\u0924\u093e\u0932 \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0947\u0936\u0928'''</td><td>1\n</td><td>2024\n</td><td>Elevated\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>'''Kanpur University Station'''\n</td>\n<td>'''\u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935\u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0932\u092f \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0947\u0936\u0928'''</td><td>1\n</td><td>2024\n</td><td>Elevated\n</td></tr>\n|}\n\n'''Phase 1'''\n\n*{{font color|Red|'''[[IIT Kanpur]]'''}}\n*[[Kalianpur railway station|Kalyanpur railway station]]\n*[[Kanpur University]]\n*Gurudev Vikas Nagar\n*Gumti No.9\n*[[Rawatpur|Rawatpur Railway Station]]\n*[[Moti Jheel]]\n\n'''Phase 2'''\n\n*Harsh Nagar\n*Chunniganj\n*[[Parade]]\n*Bada Chauraha\n*[[Phool Bagh]]\n*Birhana Road\n*Norona Crossing Sagar Market\n*[[Kanpur Central railway station]]\n*[[Kanpur Lucknow Roadways Service|ISBT Jhakarkatti]]\n*Old Transport Nagar\n*[[Kidwai Nagar|Kidwai Nagar North]]\n*[[Kidwai Nagar|Kidwai Nagar South]]\n*Yashoda Nagar\n*Baudh Nagar\n*Naubasta\n\n==={{font color|Blue|Line II (Blue Line)}} - 4 Underground, 4 Elevated===\n\n*'''[[Chandra Shekhar Azad University of Agriculture and Technology|CSA University]]'''\n*[[Ganesh Shankar Vidyarthi Memorial Medical College|GSVM Medical College]]\n*[[Rawatpur railway station]]\n*[[Kakadeo]]\n*[[Ordnance Factories Board|Vijay Nagar]]\n*[[Dada Nagar]]\n*[[Barra, Kanpur|Barra-7]]\n*[[Barra, Kanpur|Barra-8]]\n*\n\n==={{font color|Green|Line III (Green Line)}} - 7 Elevated, 3 Underground ===\n\n*'''{{font color|Green|NRI City}}'''\n*[[Allen Forest Zoo]]\n*Nawabganj\n*CSA University\n*Khalasi Line\n*Sutherganj\n*Green Park Stadium\n*District Court\n*ICA\n*'''{{font color|Green|Phool Bagh}}'''\n\n===Airport Metro===\nTo connect the upcoming terminal of [[Kanpur Airport]] at Mawaiya with the rest of the city, an airport line has been planned from the terminal to Kanpur Central railway station. The line will be underground from the station and will be elevated from Northern Railway Colony running adjacent to GT Road till Krishna Nagar station from where it will be underground with Lal Bangla and Emerald Gulistan stations in between.\n\n==Cost==\n\nThe cost of construction is estimated at \u20b911,076.48 crores for two lines. <ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Status updates==\n* '''Sept 2015:''' Proposed formation of Kanpur Metro Rail Corporation<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/city/kanpur/RITES-asked-to-make-parking-lot-at-every-Metro-station/articleshow/48982872.cms|title=RITES asked to make parking lot at every Metro station - TOI Mobile - The Times of India Mobile Site|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Nov 2015:''' Detailed project report prepared by LMRC and RITES is submitted to the state government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/kanpur-news/kanpur-metro-report-submitted-to-uttar-pradesh-government-1241598|title=Kanpur Metro Report Submitted to Uttar Pradesh Government|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Feb 2016:''' State Government is planning to lay the foundation stone of Kanpur Metro in March 2016 after state cabinet approval.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/kanpur-metro-rail-project-to-be-launched-by-march-116020801420_1.html|title=Kanpur Metro rail project to be launched by March|first=|last=IANS|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Feb 2016:''' It is expected that civil work on Kanpur metro will start by Dec 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/kanpur-varanasi-metro-rail-projects-could-start-by-december-2016-116021900701_1.html|title=Kanpur, Varanasi metro rail projects could start by December 2016|first=Virendra Singh|last=Rawat|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Mar 2016:''' Uttar Pradesh government approves the detailed project report.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://inextlive.jagran.com/kanpur-metro-file-reached-delhi-for-noc-117942|title=\u0926\u093f\u0932\u094d\u0932\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0926\u094c\u0921\u093c\u0928\u0947 \u0932\u0917\u0940 \u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u0915\u0940 \u092b\u093e\u0907\u0932 - Kanpur City News|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Mar 2016:''' Japanese team inspected the metro route in the city. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nyoooz.com/kanpur/386680/japanese-team-inspected-metro-route-in-the-city|title=Japanese team inspected metro route in the city - Kanpur NYOOOZ|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''May 2016:''' EIB ready to fund city metro project<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/city/kanpur/EIB-ready-to-fund-city-metro-project/articleshow/52038046.cms|title=EIB ready to fund city metro project - TOI Mobile - The Times of India Mobile Site|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''22 May 2016:''' Centre approves the plan for Kanpur metro <ref>{{cite web|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/transportation/railways/centre-approves-plan-for-varanasi-and-kanpur-metro/articleshow/52392309.cms|title=Centre approves plan for Varanasi and Kanpur metro - The Economic Times|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''15 June 2016:''' Last date to submit logo for Kanpur Metro by KPMRC<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kdaindia.co.in/tender.aspx|title=Kanpur Development Authority - Tenders|first=Creativ|last=Era's|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''20 July 2016:''' Scheduled inauguration of Kanpur Metro by [[Chief Minister of Uttar Pradesh]] which could not take place due to delay in giving NOCs various ministries under the Central Government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/state/uttar-pradesh/kanpur/cm-will-lay-the-foundation-stone-for-metro-project-in-kanpur-on-july-20/articleshow/53003687.cms|title=\u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 20 \u091c\u0941\u0932\u093e\u0908 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u092a\u0930\u093f\u092f\u094b\u091c\u0928\u093e \u0915\u093e \u0936\u093f\u0932\u093e\u0928\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902\u0917\u0947 \u092e\u0941\u0916\u094d\u092f\u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 - Navbharat Times|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''October 2016:''' Final approval of the Metro project by Uttar Pradesh government and [[Government of India]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/kanpur-city-14520411.html|title=\u0905\u0915\u094d\u091f\u0942\u092c\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u0915\u094b \u0938\u0948\u0926\u094d\u0927\u093e\u0902\u0924\u093f\u0915 \u0938\u0939\u092e\u0924\u093f \u0915\u0947 \u0906\u0938\u093e\u0930|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''4 October 2016:''' Foundation stone-laying ceremony done by Urban Development Minister [[Venkaiah Naidu]] in the presence of CM [[Akhilesh Yadav]] and [[BJP]] MP [[Murli Manohar Joshi]] at Brijendra Swarup Park in Benajhabar.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/National/2016-10-04/Akhilesh-Yadav-Venkaiah-Naidu-lay-foundation-stone-of-Kanpur-Metro-Rail/257059|title=Akhilesh Yadav, Venkaiah Naidu lay foundation stone of Kanpur Metro Rail|website=The Hans India}}</ref>\n* '''July 2017:''' Civil work started.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.patrika.com/news/kanpur/kanpur-metro-rail-corporation-kmrc-first-phase-construction-from-iit-to-benajhawar-1629207|title=\u092a\u093f\u0932\u0930 \u0928\u093f\u0930\u094d\u092e\u093e\u0923 \u0915\u093e \u0915\u093e\u0930\u094d\u092f \u0936\u0941\u0930\u0942, 2021 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u091f\u094d\u0930\u0948\u0915 \u092a\u0930 \u0926\u094c\u0921\u093c\u0947\u0917\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''September 2017:''' Civil engineering work comes to a halt. Central Govt has asked Kanpur Metro to rework the detailed project report and finances and asked to make it a public-private partnership model project.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amarujala.com/uttar-pradesh/kanpur/forget-the-metro-work-is-off|title=\u092b\u093f\u0932\u0939\u093e\u0932 \u092d\u0942\u0932 \u091c\u093e\u0907\u092f\u0947 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b, \u0915\u093e\u092e \u0920\u092a- Amarujala|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''October 2017:''' Work on preparing new detailed project report started. The new report is to take approximately three months.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/kanpur-city-survey-from-metro-station-with-ppp-model-16801837.html|title=\u092a\u0940\u092a\u0940\u092a\u0940 \u092e\u0949\u0921\u0932 \u0938\u0947 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u091a\u0932\u093e\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u094b \u0926\u094b\u092c\u093e\u0930\u093e \u0938\u0930\u094d\u0935\u0947|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''January 2018:''' Uttar Pradesh government cabinet decides to build metro in Kanpur, Agra, and Meerut.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/news/india/up-to-start-metro-services-in-agra-kanpur-and-meerut|title=UP to Start Metro Services in Agra, Kanpur and Meerut|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Feb 2018:''' Work started in the metro yard. Tenders floated and which are to be opened in March 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindi.nyoooz.com/news/kanpur/kanpur-metro-tender-will-open-on-march-30_197757/|title=\u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u0926\u094c\u0921\u093c\u093e\u0928\u0947 \u0915\u0940 \u0924\u0948\u092f\u093e\u0930\u0940 \u0924\u0947\u091c, 30 \u092e\u093e\u0930\u094d\u091a \u0915\u094b \u0916\u0941\u0932\u0947\u0902\u0917\u0947 \u091f\u0947\u0902\u0921\u0930 - Kanpur |publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Apr 2018:''' Center yet to approve of the Kanpur Metro project.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.financialexpress.com/infrastructure/how-metro-morphosis-is-in-works-in-yogi-adityanaths-uttar-pradesh/1117920/|title=How Metro-morphosis is in works in Yogi Adityanath\u2019s Uttar Pradesh|date=2 April 2018|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Jun 2018:''' Tendering done but not awarded as a project with a new detailed project report is yet not approved by the central government.<ref>https://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/kanpur-city-work-of-kanpur-metro-will-start-after-getting-clearance-from-central-government-18039881.html</ref>\n* '''Jun 2018:''' Finance ministry gave its in-principle approval to Kanpur metro along with Agra, Meerut, Indore, and Bhopal.\n* '''Sep 2018:''' Detailed project report sent by Uttar Pradesh government to the central government.<ref>https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/india/detailed-project-report-of-kanpur-agra-meerut-metro-sent-to-centre-2919871.html</ref>\n* '''4 Feb 2019:''' PIB approved Kanpur metro project funding.\n*'''7 Feb 2019:''' Uttar Pradesh government has allocated [[Indian rupee sign|\u20b9]]175 crores to start preliminary work in budget<ref>https://m.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/lucknow-city-kanpur-and-agra-will-soon-get-access-to-metro-18928764.html</ref>\n*'''28 February 2019:''' Centre approved Kanpur Metro costing \u20b911076.48 crores with the time limit of 5 years in construction.<ref name=\":0\" />\n* '''8 March 2019:''' PM Narendra Modi laid the foundation stone for this metro rail project<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/uttar-pradesh/kanpur/news/pm-modi-inaugrated-metro-rail-in-kanpur-take-a-dig-at-old-governments-01497159.html|title=PM Narendra Modi laid the foundation stone|access-date=2019-03-08}}</ref>\n*'''4 July 2019: ''' LMRC invites tender for construction of elevated track and stations{{cn|date=April 2020}}\n* '''Aug 2019:''' The metro route alignment is to be changed to avoid demolition of some portions of [[Ganesh Shankar Vidyarthi Memorial Medical College | GSVM Medical College]].<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kanpur/revised-metro-plan-spares-gsvm-bldgs/articleshow/70883460.cms</ref>\n*'''6 September 2019: ''' Afcons Infra awarded tender to construct 9 stations along with tracks and elevated viaduct.\n*'''20 September 2019: ''' Afcons Infra and LMRC conduct a thorough route inspection from IIT to Moti Jheel for the construction of track and metro station.\n*'''22 September 2019: ''' LMRC razes the polytechnic hostels for depot construction<ref>https://epaper.jagran.com/epaper/22-sep-2019-64-kanpur-edition-kanpur-page-6.html</ref>\n*'''8 October 2019: ''' LMRC and Afcons Infra begin with pillar construction for elevated track in front of the National Sugar institute<ref>https://epaper.jagran.com/mepaper/08-oct-2019-64-kanpur-edition-kanpur-page-5-page-5-page-5.html</ref>\n*'''15 November 2019: '''Yogi Aditya Nath, the CM of Uttar Pradesh, formally inaugurates civil work for Kanpur Metro <ref>https://epaper.jagran.com/epaper/16-nov-2019-64-kanpur-edition-kanpur-page-6.html</ref>\n*'''19 February 2020: '''Yogi Aditya Nath, the CM of Uttar Pradesh, allocates a budget of Rs 358 crores towards Kanpur metro phase 1. Construction is in full swing as UPMRC aims to complete phase 1 at a faster pace,  as compared to Lucknow metro <ref>https://epaper.jagran.com/epaper/19-feb-2020-64-kanpur-edition-kanpur-page-6.html</ref>\n*'''02 March 2020: '''Afcons Infra erected the first pier cap in record time. Construction is 3 months ahead as compared to Lucknow Metro, which is accredited with the title of being the fastest metro construction in India <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themetrorailguy.com/2020/03/03/afcons-launches-1st-pier-cap-for-kanpur-metro-line-1/|title=Afcons Launches 1st Pier Cap for Kanpur Metro Line-1|date=2020-03-03|website=The Metro Rail Guy|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-29}}</ref>\n*'''13 March 2020: '''UPMRCL opened bids for the General Consultant contract to reveal a total of 2 bidders<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themetrorailguy.com/2020/04/29/aecom-led-typsa-led-jvs-submit-gc-bids-for-kanpur-agra-metros/|title=AECOM-led & TYPSA-led JVs Submit GC Bids for Kanpur & Agra Metros|date=2020-04-29|website=The Metro Rail Guy|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-29}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Kanpur division topics}}\n{{Rapid transit in India}}\n\n{{coord missing|Uttar Pradesh}}\n\n[[Category:Proposed rapid transit in India]]\n[[Category:Transport in Kanpur]]\n[[Category:Standard gauge railways in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2016}}\n{{Infobox Public transit\n| box_width        = \n| name             = Kanpur Metro\n| image            = Kanpur Metro Map.png\n| imagesize        = 300px\n| image2           = \n| imagesize2       = \n| native_name      =\n| locale           = [[Kanpur, India|Kanpur]], [[Uttar Pradesh]], [[India]]\n| transit_type     = [[Rapid transit]]\n| lines            = 2 (Approved & Under construction, Phase I & II)\n| stations         = 30 (Approved, Phase I & II, 22 stations in a 23.785 km stretch and 8 stations in 8.6 km stretch)\n| key_people       = \n| ridership        = \n| headquarters     =  Near Uttar Pradesh State Textile Corporation Limited, [[Grand Trunk Road]], Sharda Nagar, Kanpur\n| owner            = [[ Uttar Pradesh Metro Rail Corporation]]                                  | began_operation  = December 2021 or January 2022 {phase 1} i.e.(IIT-KANPUR to Motijheel)  \n| vehicles         = \n| train_length     = 3 coaches\n| headway          = 4 minutes\n| system_length    {{convert|34.78|km|mi|abbr=on}} \n| track_gauge      = {{Track gauge|sg|allk=on}}\n| el               = 25 [[Kilovolt|Kv]] [[Electric current|AC]] [[THIRD RAIL]]\n| top_speed        = 80 km/h\n| map              = \n}}\n'''Kanpur Metro''' is a rail-based mass transit system which is under construction for the city of [[Kanpur]], [[India]], and extendable to the [[Kanpur metropolitan area]].  The feasibility study for the project was done by [[RITES]] in June 2015\n. The study was prepared to control traffic woes and congestion, which are hampering the growth, development, and prosperity of the city area. The tenders were floated for the elevated viaduct between IIT to Motijheel. [[Shapoorji Pallonji Group|AFCONS Infra]] has been awarded the tender. Elevated viaduct work has begun.The barricading has been done in the middle of the road from IIT Kanpur till Rawatpur and more than 50 pillars are constructed till 5th March,2020. The pillars are being erected and construction work is going in full swing. Construction of station near IIT has also started (dated 5th,March 2020).\n\nOn 28 February 2019, the Central government approved the metro project for [[Kanpur]] at an estimated cost of \u20b911,076.48 crores and a five-year time limit.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/business/business-news/cabinet-approves-kanpur-metro-rail-project/articleshow/68208021.cms|title=\u0915\u0948\u092c\u093f\u0928\u0947\u091f \u0928\u0947 \u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u0930\u0947\u0932 \u092a\u0930\u093f\u092f\u094b\u091c\u0928\u093e \u0915\u094b \u092e\u0902\u091c\u0942\u0930\u0940 \u0926\u0947 \u0926\u0940|date=2019-02-28|website=Navbharat Times|language=hi|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/adityanath-thanks-modi-for-clearing-agra-kanpur-metro-projects/1488020|title=Adityanath thanks Modi for clearing Agra, Kanpur Metro projects|website=outlookindia.com/|access-date=2019-02-28}}</ref> The [[European Investment Bank]] has proposed to provide a Euro 650 million loan for the project.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://themetrorailguy.com/2020/03/31/eib-evaluating-e650mn-loan-for-kanpur-metro-phase-1/|title=EIB Evaluating \u20ac650 mn Loan for Kanpur Metro Phase 1|date=2020-03-31|website=The Metro Rail Guy|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-02}}</ref>\n\n==Corridors==\n\n==={{font color|Red|Line I (Red Line)}} - 8 Underground, 14 Elevated===\n== Stations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\" width=\"100%\" \n|-\n! style=\"background:#FFDF00;\" colspan=\"9\" | <span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Line-1'''</span>\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''#'''</span>\n! colspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Station Name'''</span>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Phase'''</span>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Opening'''</span>\n! rowspan=\"2\" |<span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Station Layout'''</span><tr>\n<th><span style=\"color:Black;\">'''English'''</span></th>\n<th><span style=\"color:Black;\">'''Hindi'''</span></th></tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>'''IIT Kanpur Station'''\n</td>\n<td>'''\u0906\u0908\u0906\u0908\u091f\u0940 \u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0947\u0936\u0928'''</td><td>1\n</td><td>2024\n</td><td>Elevated\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>'''Kalyanpur Railway Station'''\n</td>\n<td>'''\u0915\u0932\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0923\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u0930\u0947\u0932\u0935\u0947 \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0947\u0936\u0928 '''</td><td>1\n</td><td>2024\n</td><td>Elevated\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>'''SPM Hospital Station'''\n</td>\n<td>'''\u090f\u0938\u092a\u0940\u090f\u092e \u0905\u0938\u094d\u092a\u0924\u093e\u0932 \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0947\u0936\u0928'''</td><td>1\n</td><td>2024\n</td><td>Elevated\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>'''Kanpur University Station'''\n</td>\n<td>'''\u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935\u0935\u093f\u0926\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0932\u092f \u0938\u094d\u091f\u0947\u0936\u0928'''</td><td>1\n</td><td>2024\n</td><td>Elevated\n</td></tr>\n|}\n\n'''Phase 1'''\n\n*{{font color|Red|'''[[IIT Kanpur]]'''}}\n*[[Kalianpur railway station|Kalyanpur railway station]]\n*[[Kanpur University]]\n*Gurudev Vikas Nagar\n*Gumti No.9\n*[[Rawatpur|Rawatpur Railway Station]]\n*[[Moti Jheel]]\n\n'''Phase 2'''\n\n*Harsh Nagar\n*Chunniganj\n*[[Parade]]\n*Bada Chauraha\n*[[Phool Bagh]]\n*Birhana Road\n*Norona Crossing Sagar Market\n*[[Kanpur Central railway station]]\n*[[Kanpur Lucknow Roadways Service|ISBT Jhakarkatti]]\n*Old Transport Nagar\n*[[Kidwai Nagar|Kidwai Nagar North]]\n*[[Kidwai Nagar|Kidwai Nagar South]]\n*Yashoda Nagar\n*Baudh Nagar\n*Naubasta\n\n==={{font color|Blue|Line II (Blue Line)}} - 4 Underground, 4 Elevated===\n\n*'''[[Chandra Shekhar Azad University of Agriculture and Technology|CSA University]]'''\n*[[Ganesh Shankar Vidyarthi Memorial Medical College|GSVM Medical College]]\n*[[Rawatpur railway station]]\n*[[Kakadeo]]\n*[[Ordnance Factories Board|Vijay Nagar]]\n*[[Dada Nagar]]\n*[[Barra, Kanpur|Barra-7]]\n*[[Barra, Kanpur|Barra-8]]\n*\n\n==={{font color|Green|Line III (Green Line)}} - 7 Elevated, 3 Underground ===\n\n*'''{{font color|Green|NRI City}}'''\n*[[Allen Forest Zoo]]\n*Nawabganj\n*CSA University\n*Khalasi Line\n*Sutherganj\n*Green Park Stadium\n*District Court\n*ICA\n*'''{{font color|Green|Phool Bagh}}'''\n\n===Airport Metro===\nTo connect the upcoming terminal of [[Kanpur Airport]] at Mawaiya with the rest of the city, an airport line has been planned from the terminal to Kanpur Central railway station. The line will be underground from the station and will be elevated from Northern Railway Colony running adjacent to GT Road till Krishna Nagar station from where it will be underground with Lal Bangla and Emerald Gulistan stations in between.\n\n==Cost==\n\nThe cost of construction is estimated at \u20b911,076.48 crores for two lines. <ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Status updates==\n* '''Sept 2015:''' Proposed formation of Kanpur Metro Rail Corporation<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/city/kanpur/RITES-asked-to-make-parking-lot-at-every-Metro-station/articleshow/48982872.cms|title=RITES asked to make parking lot at every Metro station - TOI Mobile - The Times of India Mobile Site|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Nov 2015:''' Detailed project report prepared by LMRC and RITES is submitted to the state government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ndtv.com/kanpur-news/kanpur-metro-report-submitted-to-uttar-pradesh-government-1241598|title=Kanpur Metro Report Submitted to Uttar Pradesh Government|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Feb 2016:''' State Government is planning to lay the foundation stone of Kanpur Metro in March 2016 after state cabinet approval.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/kanpur-metro-rail-project-to-be-launched-by-march-116020801420_1.html|title=Kanpur Metro rail project to be launched by March|first=|last=IANS|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Feb 2016:''' It is expected that civil work on Kanpur metro will start by Dec 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business-standard.com/article/economy-policy/kanpur-varanasi-metro-rail-projects-could-start-by-december-2016-116021900701_1.html|title=Kanpur, Varanasi metro rail projects could start by December 2016|first=Virendra Singh|last=Rawat|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Mar 2016:''' Uttar Pradesh government approves the detailed project report.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://inextlive.jagran.com/kanpur-metro-file-reached-delhi-for-noc-117942|title=\u0926\u093f\u0932\u094d\u0932\u0940 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u0926\u094c\u0921\u093c\u0928\u0947 \u0932\u0917\u0940 \u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u0915\u0940 \u092b\u093e\u0907\u0932 - Kanpur City News|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''Mar 2016:''' Japanese team inspected the metro route in the city. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nyoooz.com/kanpur/386680/japanese-team-inspected-metro-route-in-the-city|title=Japanese team inspected metro route in the city - Kanpur NYOOOZ|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''May 2016:''' EIB ready to fund city metro project<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.timesofindia.com/city/kanpur/EIB-ready-to-fund-city-metro-project/articleshow/52038046.cms|title=EIB ready to fund city metro project - TOI Mobile - The Times of India Mobile Site|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''22 May 2016:''' Centre approves the plan for Kanpur metro <ref>{{cite web|url=http://economictimes.indiatimes.com/industry/transportation/railways/centre-approves-plan-for-varanasi-and-kanpur-metro/articleshow/52392309.cms|title=Centre approves plan for Varanasi and Kanpur metro - The Economic Times|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''15 June 2016:''' Last date to submit logo for Kanpur Metro by KPMRC<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kdaindia.co.in/tender.aspx|title=Kanpur Development Authority - Tenders|first=Creativ|last=Era's|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''20 July 2016:''' Scheduled inauguration of Kanpur Metro by [[Chief Minister of Uttar Pradesh]] which could not take place due to delay in giving NOCs various ministries under the Central Government.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.navbharattimes.indiatimes.com/state/uttar-pradesh/kanpur/cm-will-lay-the-foundation-stone-for-metro-project-in-kanpur-on-july-20/articleshow/53003687.cms|title=\u0915\u093e\u0928\u092a\u0941\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 20 \u091c\u0941\u0932\u093e\u0908 \u0915\u094b \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u092a\u0930\u093f\u092f\u094b\u091c\u0928\u093e \u0915\u093e \u0936\u093f\u0932\u093e\u0928\u094d\u092f\u093e\u0938 \u0915\u0930\u0947\u0902\u0917\u0947 \u092e\u0941\u0916\u094d\u092f\u092e\u0902\u0924\u094d\u0930\u0940 - Navbharat Times|publisher=}}</ref>\n* '''October 2016:''' Final approval of the Metro project by Uttar Pradesh government and [[Government of India]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://m.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/kanpur-city-14520411.html|title=\u0905\u0915\u094d\u091f\u0942\u092c\u0930 \u092e\u0947\u0902 \u092e\u0947\u091f\u094d\u0930\u094b \u0915\u094b \u0938\u0948\u0926\u094d\u0927\u093e\u0902\u0924\u093f\u0915 \u0938\u0939